\begin_layout Subsubsection
Decision Tree
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This approach aims to model the relationships between the input data and
 the resulting output.
 Used for classification purposes with discrete outputs by use of class
 labels.
 The logic-structure consists of nodes that represent features and branches
 that represent the values of the features.
 The leaf nodes represent the class labels The resultant trees are used
 to create Rules, that the Smart-Home system can use to classify the current-sta
te of residents as safe or at potential risk by calculating the class labels.
 Such a system is also known as Rule-Based-System(RBS).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Trees can be built through an induction process by running algorithms on
 a dataset.
 Some known algorithms used are - TDIDT/ID3, C4.5, CART, MARS, and CHAID.
 Trees can be generated by recursive algorithms that grow the tree and algorithm
s that prune the tree dynamically.
 Algorithms like C4.5 and CART employ both: growing and pruning of the tree.
 It is important to note that the accuracy of any algorithm is not absolute,
 but rather varies case-to-case basis.
 
\end_layout

