\begin_layout Subsubsection
Conditional Random field
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Conditional Random Fields are based on ‘Discriminative graphical Models’
 in contrast to above mentioned generative classifiers (Hidden Markov) and
 are used to find hidden states and transitions from the observed data sequences.
 CRF primarily works on only Conditional Probability calculations rather
 than Joint-Probability.
 It is also flexible enough to accept arbitrary and dependent relations
 between the sequences of observations.
 Unlike HMM, CRF also discards the assumption of independent variables,
 allowing it to capture virtually any relationships between an observation-varia
ble and the hidden-states.
 
